        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 5:31PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles south of Broadus to 7 miles
southwest of Biddle, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Localized wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail, along
with moderate rainfall and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Biddle and Belle Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
